org.orgName: Western District Court of Washington, Northern Division

div1.p: UNITED STATES DISTRICT COURT WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON NORTHERN DIVISION
In the Matter of the Application of Chin Quock Wah for a Writ of Habeas Corpus ) NO. 2.971 ORDER.

Upon the motion of Albert Moodie, Assistant United States Attorney, for the Western District of Washington, it appearing that there has been deposited in the Registry of this Court the sum of One Hundred Dollars, to cover expense of maintenance of the petitioner in the above entitled cause, same having been deposited by John J. Sullivan, Esq., attorney for petitioner; and it further appearing from the affidavit of Henry M. White, Commissioner of Immigration, hereto attached, that the attached bill in favor of J.Richard Lane in the sum of Fifty-nine and 20/100 Dollars ($59.20) is a just bill, and the court being advised that J.Richard Lane mentioned in the affidavit is the same party who funished meals to the petitioner is the above entitled cause, and being fully advised in the premises;

IT IS HEREBY ORDERED that the Clerk of the Court pay to the said J.Richard Lane, the sum of Fifty-nine and 20/100 Dollards ($59.20), and deduct from the balance the sum of One Dollar as one per cent commission on the original deposit of One Hundred Dollars, and that the final balance be held pending final settlement of this case paid to John J Sullivan - Atty for Petitioner
div1.ab: Jeremiah Neterer United States District Judge
Wh. John J Sullivan Atty for Pet.
div1.p: TO J.RICHARD LANE DR 644 CENTRAL BUILDING
For meals furnished at U.S. Immigration Station, Seattle, during the months of March, April, May and June, 1915.
Chin Quock Wah March 4 before B to June 10 after Dinner 296 meals @20¢ $59.20
